<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-89-0347 </DOCNO><TEXT>AERO is a useful program for aerosol scientists and engineers. It providesa handy tool for back of the envelope type calculations for a varietyroutine aerosol problems. Most of the calculations are CGS units. Theprogram is run by typing BASICA AERO. The following menu of subroutinesappears: 1. Gas parameters 2. Particle/flow parameters 3. Impactor parameters4. Diffusion parameters 5. Condensation and evaporation 6. Droplet breakup7. Coagulation 8. Electrical properties 9. Particle loss in tubes andvessels.</TEXT></DOC>